DataElement.preferredDefinition: A time value that represents a period of time measured in sixtieths of a minute.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The partial time (hour, minute, or second) value.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Partial; being or affecting only a part; not total

Concepts.definition: Being or affecting only a part of something.

Property.preferredDefinition: Time is the continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.  It may also refer to a specific point in this continuum or to the interval separating two points.  It is generally measured in minutes, days, months, or years.

Concepts.definition: The continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.  [Explanatory comment: The preferred exchange format for Seconds is ss.uuuu where ss=seconds and uuuu=fractional seconds. The values for Seconds are numbers between 00 and 59. Optional Fractional Seconds may have the integers (0 to 9) in any position. Fractional Seconds may be provided to the precision of 1 to 4 characters. The display format for Seconds and Fractional Seconds information is determined by programmatic requirements.]

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Time is the continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.  It may also refer to a specific point in this continuum or to the interval separating two points.  It is generally measured in minutes, days, months, or years.

Concepts.definition: The continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.

ReferenceDocuments.name: Date/Time Documentation
ReferenceDocuments.description: Definition of basic generic data elements for exchange of Date and Time information.

ReferenceDocuments.name: 1-COMMENT
ReferenceDocuments.description: The preferred exchange format for Seconds and Fractional Seconds is ss.uuuu. For single digit values, the value must be preceded with a zero. The optional fractional seconds information should be preceded by a decimal and appended to the full time specification. Fractional seconds may be provided to the precision of 1 to 4 characters. The display format for Seconds and Fractional Seconds information is determined by programmatic requirements.
